      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Cruise control Combination switch removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "1084_3.0_jpn_11347576_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Loosen screw (A). Disconnect the coupler (B) and remove the cruise control combination switch (C)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Work with care to prevent the screw from falling out."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "1084_3.0_jpn_11390146_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Remove the cruise control combination switch (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Cruise control Combination switch Check"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "1084_3.0_jpn_11037441_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Measure the resistance between terminals No. 2 and No. 5 in each position according to the table. If it is out of the standard value, replace the cruise control combination switch. position Resistance value OFF Approx. 2.2kΩ CRUISE button (press) Approx. 60Ω CANCEL button (press) Approx. 183Ω SET - button (press) Approx. 446Ω RES + button (press) Approx. 892Ω"
    }
  ],
